<p>The <code>@firstFieldValue</code> property returns the value of the first field in the current record.</p>

<h2>Get First Field Value</h2>
<pre>{open}users{close}
  {open}@first{close}
    Primary value: {open}@firstFieldValue{close}
  {open}/@first{close}
{open}/users{close}</pre>

<p>Result:</p>
{users}
  {@first}
    Primary value: {@firstFieldValue}
  {/@first}
{/users}

<h2>All First Values</h2>
<pre>{open}users{close}
  ID: {open}@firstFieldValue{close}
{open}/users{close}</pre>

<p>Result:</p>
<div>
{users}
  ID: {@firstFieldValue}<br>
{/users}
</div>
